properties.Comment: Traffic at this intersection often goes through stop signs without stopping or initiates rolling stops. Cars also speed on both 40th and Reservoir, making it dangerous to cross this intersection via car, foot, bike, anything.
properties.Name: Carrie G

properties.Comment: Cars heading east on 40th often do not stop at the stop sign at the corner of 40th and Tyler (bottom of hill). This has been observed by residents on many occasions and is particularly dangerous because Ostrander Park is at that intersection, creating a particular hazard for children.
properties.Name: Carrie G.

properties.Comment: Drivers coming up Gould Avenue turning onto Reservoir Blvd frequently do not stop at the Gould Ave. stop sign and nearly cause accidents as they turn onto Reservoir. This has become more of an issue now that there is more foot traffic coming from Ratio and the library.
properties.Name: Carrie G.

properties.Comment: Drivers going both ways (north bound and south bound) on Reservoir Blvd frequently speed, oftentimes at near highway speeds. We have to ask for speed traffic monitoring every year but the problem has only gotten worse over the years. There are no "pinch" points on Reservoir so people go really fast on this road because visually it is wide and long and gives the visual of being a high speed county road. This street is lined with houses and makes it dangerous and noisy to live on it due to the traffic.
properties.Name: Carrie G.

properties.Comment: The entirety of Reservoir Blvd has speeding traffic on it. After 41st ave, there are no sidewalks so pedestrians have to walk on the road with traffic (which means many pedestrians can't/won't walk on it because it's dangerous). Reservoir Blvd is a particular frustration because when we have asked the city for help calming traffic in the past, we've been told it's not a street that Heights can control, but if you call Hennepin County/Minneapolis, they *also* say they have no control over it.
properties.Name: Carrie G

properties.Comment: Cars turning West onto Gould from Reservoir drive on Gould as if it's. one way street (there are no street lines on Gould). It has nearly caused head on crashes on multiple occasions.
properties.Name: Carrie G

properties.Comment: Comment for the entirety of Central Avenue in Heights--this road has too fast of traffic, people go through stop lights, crosswalks are dangerous, pedestrians cross randomly outside of crosswalks (and crosswalks are spaced far apart which encourages people to cross anywhere). There are accidents on Central frequently,  often fatal. It's like a highway running through the city causing safety/noise/pollution issues.
properties.Name: Carrie G

properties.Comment: 53rd and University is a super dangerous intersection. The frontage road adds to the congestion, lots of speeding cars, intersections blocked, accidents, and near hits of pedestrians and bicyclists.

Many cars use this alley as a "road" instead of driving up to Reservoir Blvd. This makes the alley dangerous for residents to be in their driveways and the many people that use the alley for walking. The alley traffic has increased since the City Hall Apartments were built on Gould / Central Avenue.
properties.Name: Josh G.

properties.Comment: There are many uncontrolled intersections on 6th street which I have almost been hit at. We need to get the funding to put in stop signs.
There is no stop sign in either direction at this four-way intersection, and its already a somewhat blind intersection
properties.Name: Emily

properties.Comment: People making illegal Uturns, not stopping at the stop signs. People going the wrong way on the one way.
properties.Name: Cassandra

properties.Comment: This light needs to sense traffic coming from 53rd onto Central.  I sat there for 8 minutes waiting for the light to turn green when on 53rd to make a left or go threw to Menards..
properties.Name: Rick Reichert

properties.Comment: No sidewalks on this street, even though it is a route to school and has high speed traffic
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: Very high speed traffic on this street, suggest adding speed bump or calming of some kind
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: Bike line is in terrible repair, and barely connects to anything. In fact there are almost no N-S biking lanes of any kind in CH or NE, it's all E-W
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: Totally uncontrolled intersection, but the standard in most of NE is two way stops, so it's very dangerous when everyone assumes the other direction has a stop sign
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: Tyler or Polk would be really good candidates for a bike lane, instead of the faster and more dangerous route on reservoir. It would be a good way to get to the 37th Ave trail and then to Columbia Park
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: Please add flags to make it easier to get driver's attention when crossing to school. It's dangerous especially when the sun is at certain angles.
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: All of these frontage road intersections are confusing with no guidance. At least add some signage for who has the right of way, where to wait for lights to change, etc.
properties.Name: Alex Magidow

properties.Comment: People drive way too fast. Lots of kids. No sidewalks. City refuses to add speed bumps because they're inconvenient for snow clouds.
properties.Name: Andy newton

properties.Comment: Lots of walkers.  Lots of kids. No sidewalks
properties.Name: andrew newton

properties.Comment: Cars driving E W on 42nd should not go straight across Central or make left hand turns here. Completely block of with median or only allow left.hand turns off of central with special turn lane.
The design of this road, especially with its with and downhill, make people drive way too fast. It also doesn't have striping which would help.
A lot of youth bike this road to school. It's one of the main ways around the reservoir for neighborhood kids. I would like to see it dedicated bike lane
All of these uncontrolled intersections are constantly seeing near misses. It makes it scary to bike, walk, or drive here

properties.Name: Steve Forseth

properties.Comment: ADD a "No Pedestrian Crossing" Sign here!  For those walker crossing from East to West across Central Ave. here, THERE IS NO SIGNAGE FACING THEM SAYING NO PEDESTRIANS!!! properties.Name: Steve Forseth

properties.Comment: ADD a large "No Pedestrian Crossing" Sign here!  (The only sign is a tiny one located in the middle median ... and that's not enough because folks are still crossing Central here)   [Walkers should use the Pedestrian Bridge!!!}

properties.Comment: There is a 'No Pedestrian Crossing" sign here, but it's too tiny!  Please mount a LARGER sign instead for those walking across Central Avenue, so they know they should not be crossing here.  They should use the pedestrian bridge instead!
properties.Name: Steve Forseth

properties.Comment: it's tough to walk this corner with cars going fast around a blind corner
properties.Name: Teresa

properties.Comment: there are sometimes road construction or large vehicles parked at this corner. it makes driving around it quite precarious not knowing if oncoming traffic is ahead.
busy street with no sidewalks. would like this to be more walkable.
many cars driving fast down this road even when there are multiple vehicles parked on either side. would love to see sidewalks here on this street

Generally difficult to safely cross from Polk onto 43rd without sidewalks and few stop signs. especially with small children. The condition of this road area is littered with shallow potholes which also makes it difficult to  pass with small wheels.
Very sharp intersection going both ways. Could use some chevron corner signs. there are often tire tracks on either side of this corner in the winter.
Why does the sidewalk end here? Such a bummer.
This intersection neefs flashing lights on the stop signs on Cry Rd E so it's more visible and noticable for drivers so they'll actually stop at the intersection.
properties.Name: Add flashing lights on the stop signs

properties.Comment: Add a flashing lights crosswalk to help alert drivers to pedestrians who ate hard to see with the curved road.
properties.Name: Add cross walk with flash lights bitton

properties.Comment: Left Tues from 43rd on to south bound Central Ave can block the entrances to businesses. Then cars have to wait to turn and it blocks everything up. People get frustrated and pull out on to Central causing even more danger to other cars and people crossing even though there is not a crosswalk at this intersection

Uncontrolled intersection where there have been several near-misses. Especially scary since this is a bus stop for kids  and several kids live at this intersection where cars speed through without even slowing down, let alone yielding to cars coming from the other direction.

Uncontrolled intersection where there have been several accidents and near misses. Drivers do not understand how to drive through uncontrolled intersections, because they don't know its uncontrolled. Its incredibly dangerous.
I would love more sidewalks in this area, but especially on Fillmore Street here and 46th heading to Keyes Park. Those are actually fairly busy roads and it would feel safer to walk on a sidewalk.
properties.Name: Alex Cohen

properties.Comment: It is very difficult to turn left onto central from 45th in either direction. It is often unclear whether oncoming traffic is intending to turn or not, even with individual turn signals. Additionally, while the balusters hopefully make pedestrian crossing safer, they definitely get in the way of a left turn, further increasing the difficulty and confusion on turning onto central.
properties.Name: Alex Cohen

properties.Comment: Stinson Blvd and Innsbruck Parkway are used by many people to walk and bike. Traffic on both roads has increased and drivers are driving way too fast and not stopping at the stop sign in Stinson and Innsbruck. The road should have speed bumps to slow traffic or a four way stop on Stinson and Innsbruck.
properties.Name: Renee Sawyer

properties.Comment: Drivers often speed through this area. A new speed camera was put up near University, but adding speed limit signs, maybe alongside a sign informing of photo enforcement could help.
properties.Name: Sam Rinne

properties.Comment: Lots of pedestrians and bicyclists use 44th, but are forced to use the shoulder on either side as there is no sidewalk past Jackson St. A sidewalk expansion or even a paved path would be beneficial, especially if/when the former Rainbow Foods site is redeveloped with new businesses.
properties.Name: Sam Rinne

properties.Comment: There should be a sidewalk on one side of 45 1/2 Ave NE leading to Keyes Park. The street is constantly busy with children on bikes, walking on foot, often by themselves to go play at the park. Sadly there are cars that whip up and down the street far too fast, and the need for better pedestrian safety is high. The sidewalk should connect to the path at the park that currently drops pedestrians into the culdesac.
properties.Name: Elisabeth Morley

properties.Comment: A stop sign is needed on 45 1/2 Ave NE at Fillmore. Too many cars don't yield to cross traffic.
properties.Name: Elisabeth Morley

properties.Comment: Bike paths along Arthur street are in very bad shape
No sidewalks - cars often parked in bike lanes leaving walkers to cut out into traffic lanes

Could comment for all the possibilities here (walking, driving, rolling). Chatham is an extremely long and wide street that essentially spans 3-4 normal city blocks. Drivers will routinely travel down this road at 50+ mph due to their being no traffic calming measures whatsoever. This is super concerning given the amount of families and children that try to utilize the road, especially given the close proximity to one of the middle schools and the high school. There needs to be a sidewalk added, the driving lanes narrowed, and also some kind of slowing/stop mechanism at the corner of Chatham and Golf. I routinely worry about seeing a pedestrian vs car fatality on this street

No sidewalks on 45th make it difficult to walk/bike. It is a common route of travel as just across the city border in New Brighton has a sidewalk on the North side of the county road, and it is a connector from Reservoir

Not only do cars travel at high rates of speed on Reservoir due to the wide design of the road and only one stop at 40th, but lack of sidewalks and cars parking in the bike lanes leave pedestrians to jut into traffic to continue. This is especially true with disabled residents who rely on the bus route that travels this street

Cars traveling S to N here are often missed by cars traveling E to W due to there being a hill on the S side of the intersection, obstructing brush on the SW corner, and the offset nature of the four-way intersection

Have almost seen a few accidents here from cars traveling S down Upland Crest, as it is hard to manage oncoming N bound traffic on Heights Drive as well as turning almost 180 degrees to look at S bound traffic on Heights. Only a yield sign here
No sidewalks on all os Stinson. Common travel route as New Brighton has sidewalks coming up to Heights on County Road E and 5th St
The biking/walking lane on the E side of the road is so tiny, and cars travel at fast speeds down this road.
Sidewalk abruptly stops heading Eastward
No sidewalks on Johnson leading up to 37th

Intersection needs to be made safer in general with longer crossing times, less lanes. Also the pedestrian land bridge is an idea to promote safety, but if the goal is to have it used there needs to be deterrents to people crossing at road level
No sidewalks connecting Reservioir to County Road E/anything Eastward

Cars travel at fast speeds N and S on Reservoir, and many cars enter from 44th on to Reservoir, making it hard to make a left turn from 44th to Reservoir or Reservoir to 44th. Only stop is on 44th heading W. Could benefit from an all way stop or roundabout
No sidewalks leading from Central to Sullivan Lake. With redevelopment of Central coming and also possibly redevelopment of the Medtronic site, this could be a popular route
Should have the sidewalk link up with the trail here
Should have sidewalks leading up to all parks, especially here (only has one small strip)
Sidewalk is extremely narrow on S side and has lighting poles in the middle. Also 44th not having a complete connected sidewalk/trail from University to Reservoir needs to be addressed

Have nearly been hit by a car multiple times trying to cross university Ave to get to the bus stop. The green light for westbound traffic on 40th turns green at the same time as the walk sign, causing drivers to turn without watching for pedestrians crossing university. Change the green light to stay red until the cross walk signal is done.
properties.Name: Jeremiah Laughlin

properties.Comment: People do not understand yield signs and fly through here without slowing down and yielding. This has high foot traffic due to the Mosque and is dangerous to walk or drive through (see history of accidents at this intersection).
properties.Name: Jeremiah Laughlin

properties.Comment: People do not understand yield signs and fly through here without slowing down. This is a high foot traffic area due to the Church nearby. Consider stop signs on north and south traffic.
properties.Name: Jeremiah Laughlin

properties.Comment: I would love to bike around Columbia Heights more, but do not feel safe along central or crossing central as people use it as a free way to commute from downtown to the suburbs. It needs safe bike paths off the road or separated from the road by physical barriers. That would help with other roads as well, but central is the most dangerous.
properties.Name: Jeremiah Laughlin

properties.Comment: No sidewalks here for East/West walkers. Would help make the neighborhood more walkable.
properties.Name: Jeremiah Laughlin

properties.Comment: I appreciate the city putting a pylon in the middle of this crosswalk informing cars that they must yield to pedestrians. About 1/4th of cars actually follow it in my experience crossing here daily. Adding another yellow neon sign or flashing light would increase safety of crossing here.
properties.Name: Jeremiah Laughlin

properties.Comment: Humongous intersection for no reason. Eighty feet across if you are crossing Hart on the south side of 39th. No sidewalks. Adjacent to 55+ community.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Crosswalks are longer than the width of the street. Streets are 40-45 feet wide an the crosswalks are 60-80 feet long. Applies to Reservoir, Tyler, Polk intersections.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Wide turn radii in a residential area with many pedestrians, children playing, and waiting for the school bus. Turns should be much tighter so that cars need to slow down while turning.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Bike lanes should be moved inside of parking so that the parked cars protect the bike lanes. Pavement of bike lanes in very rough condition.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Busy area for cars and pedestrians missing marked crosswalk. Crossing distance for pedestrians is very long. Should be a comfortable boulevard to take a stroll and not a highway.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: No sidewalk and only shoulder on one side of the street makes it impossible to safely walk on Johnson.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: This section of Stinson going to the swimming beach is narrow with no sidewalks but has a steep hill so many drivers speed down the hill. Meanwhile there are many people walking to the beach from their car parked on the side of the road. The city needs to work with Silverwood to put a nice trail to the beach.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Hard to drive east or west, or exit school lot during school drop off and pick up with people stopping and dropping off kids right on street when backed up.
Impossible to cross in crosswalk to get to school as drivers will not stop unless someone is directing traffic which is not every day.
More often than not, I am seeing drivers run stop sign here.

Walking is nerve wracking all along 44th avenue because of the lack of barrier or sidewalk.  Cars going fast and completely ignoring stop signs as pedestrians try to cross.  We even had a car try not stop for us (walking pedestrians) at the stop sign with a police car behind them. I had to walk out and risk them hitting me for them to actually stop.
Cars continue to speed and not stop for pedestrians from University to Central along 40th.
Cars continue to slide through intersection in winter due to too high of speed when approaching stop sign and inadequate salting/sanding.

Constantly feeling unsafe when crossing here all seasons.  4 out of 5 cars do not stop for pedestrians.  Perhaps you could do a study with people documenting stops.  Nerve racking with all the kids going to Murzyn Hall, the boxing gym, the park in both the summer and winter (sledding).
Cars don't stop when walkers try to cross 40th.
Light does not change for regular cars here unless a car is across central waiting to go straight or turn south. Please adjust.

Would love actual bike lane going north/south length of city not 65 or 47.  It is difficult for kids/preteens to ride on sidewalks of all kinds of disrepair and would love a designated bike lane. The kids on this side have to get to school and there are areas where it is not safe to walk or bike.

Not sure how pedestrian, especially kids walking to school are supposed to do so safely when there is not a sidewalk or walk/bike lane on either side on the street here. It is unsafe when it is down to one lane between 46th and 47th and no one should have to walk on someone's lawn or the mulch of the weeds. These kids are required to get to school and some of them have to have the most direct way as they are still learning.
I would love a bike lane to ride safely and have kids ride safely on the right side of the road when there is not room for both a car and a bike at the same time.
It might confuse people that this has not been the name of the park for quite some time.
Too many ppl run the stop sign
Horrible intersection for pedestrians
properties.Name: Nw

properties.Comment: The walk lights across university never give people enough time to cross.
A stop sign. People drive so fast from 40th or 37th without having to slow down.
properties.Name: Jennifer  Pyper-Muno

properties.Comment: 39th is a narrow road with no sidewalk. When cars are parked on both sides it's a single lane road and makes it hard to walk on it safely. I would love a sidewalk on one side.
properties.Name: Jennifer  Pyper-Muno

properties.Comment: A sidewalk on this road on one side at least would make it safer to walk on esp as you get closer to silver lane with the curve in the road.
properties.Name: Jennifer  Pyper-Muno

properties.Comment: Hayes ave NE between 39th and 37th avenues has seen an increase motor vehicle speeds with many adults, children and pets being at risk.
properties.Name: Glenn Witte

properties.Comment: The angle of the intersection makes it difficult to view both directions of traffic when turning left from Polk. Streets should intersect 39th at a right (or close to right) angle. Applies to Tyler & Polk @ 39th, 40th, 41st, etc.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment:
The City's "Recommended Bike Route Network" says that Jefferson has as "existing bike route on road," which apparently refers to the painted should on one side of the road. The city should either remove Jefferson from the route map or put in safe bike treatments. I would prefer to make this a safe route for bicycles as I ride nearby often.

Shoulders are a fine bike treatment in a rural context but in a city with parking the shoulder is not safe bike infrastructure.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Many pedestrians need to cross this street but there is no light and 5 lanes of traffic to cross. It is not safe and there needs to be a marked crosswalks with RRFBs or something.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Many pedestrians need to cross this street but there is no light and 5 lanes of traffic to cross. It is not safe and there needs to be a marked crosswalks with RRFBs or something.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Many pedestrians need to cross this street (busy bus stop) but there is no light and 5 lanes of traffic to cross. It is not safe and there needs to be a marked crosswalks with RRFBs or something.
properties.Name: Jared Finkelson

properties.Comment: Make this road narrower and sidewalks on both sides of 49th. People drive too fast on this road.
properties.Name: Nic Ahmadvand

properties.Comment: Have more crosswalks crossing 49th
Have a better crosswalk with flashing lights for this entry/exit point.
properties.Name: Nic Ahmadvand

properties.Comment: There are a lot of potholes starting in the 45th to the 49th. The city keeps adding asphalt but it doesn't last long. We should rebuild the whole street.
properties.Name: Fabricio Orellana

properties.Comment: More sidewalks are needed for walking in this area.
The yield sign on 6th street isn't being paid attention to.  I use 48th Ave a lot and have almost been hit several times.  The yield sign should be turned into a stop sign
properties.Name: Becky Wietecha

properties.Comment: This has to be one of the worst intersections on University Ave due to the amount of traffic on 44th Ave.  Both in the way of driving and walking.
properties.Name: Becky Wietecha

properties.Comment: Cars frequently use shoulder/parking lane as right turn lane when turning from 49th onto university or frontage road. It works well, so maybe consider permanently designating that as a right turn lane via either signage or paint.

A Trail would be nice to see along the West side of Main St from 37th Ave to 40th Ave, with Fridley connecting their portion from 40th to 44th since theirs is already in place from 44th to 57th. Lastly Minneapolis connecting the rest from 37th to St. Anthony Pkwy to meet up with the trail system along St Anthony Pkwy
properties.Name: Brad W

properties.Comment: People often speed on this stretch of road right at the entrance of the park. It is dangerous for pedestrians, esp children. There needs to be a stop sign here.
properties.Name: Jon B

properties.Comment: Fix tennis courts. They are unusable and in very bad shape. Maybe a basketball court? Or a new tennis court?
properties.Name: Jon b

properties.Comment: 49th ave needs sidewalks. Very dangerous for pedestrians.
Streets are unnecessarily wide. Please add sidewalks for pedestrians. I feel scared every time I walk with my kids that a car will hit us.
there should be a stop sign here..there have been many accidents.
could there be speed bumps on this road? cars are slowed on the other side, but coming from this way, cars come in fast and don't always see the new cross walk
crosswalk is awkward and cars don't stop for pedestrians here. Need a stop sign or speed bump.

Bus stop here causes issues with transit since this intersection is a defacto pedestrian crossing due to the opposing transit stops.  The NB bus stop should move to 44th Ave before the light.  This benefits everyone due to a stoplight control, a marked crosswalk, and a predictable stopping area for both cars and pedestrians. The SB bus stop should be imrpoved with the proposed development of this empty parcel by moving it to a bump out protected bus  stop, especially considering the future development will be mixed use with hopefull a grocery store that will produce more transit traffic.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: With the amount of pedestrian traffic here, and the existance of a concrete island, add a mid-block marked crosswalk with pedestrian- controlled crossing signal (like what exists on Johnson street just north of 18th ave) so that people visiting the library, city hall, DMV, theater, etc all have safe mid-block crossings.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: Add a marked cross walk to continue the train across 40th to the bike lanes/parking.  Also, this section of 40th could benefit from protected bike lanes to connect to the "downtown" district of CH with Reservoir Road, which has a nice bike lane.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: Add a marked cross walk to continue the train across 40th to the bike lanes/parking.  Also, this section of 40th could benefit from protected bike lanes to connect to the "downtown" district of CH with Reservoir Road, which has a nice bike lane.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: Pavement on Reservoir needs improvement, especially in shoulder area.  I bike this area almost daily, and I cannot use the bike lanes in many areas due to pavement condition.  I would also  recommend emulating Minneapolis and painting bike lanes GREEN for improved visibility.    This is true for the ENTIRE stretch of Reservoir.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: The pull in for the transit station tends to cause near miss collisions and traffic issues due to the angle.  I do not have a proposed solution, but this should be examined on how to improve this transit station.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: The width of 44th avenue would be awesome to use for marked bike lanes that could connect the river trail on Main Street to reservoir road bike lanes.  Eventually connecting to Silverlake Park.  44th Avenue is an excellent cooridor for biking and pedestrians, but the pavement needs improvement and better markings.
properties.Name: Joey Diaz

properties.Comment: PLEASE add a stopilight at this intersection.  PLease add marked crosswalks at this intersection.  You are planning a major development at the rainbow site and the placement of transit stops, traffic patterns, and where pedestrians ACTUALLY cross means that you should design this interstion based on exisiting traffic patterns instead of trying to fight them.  Ever see the meme picture of a sidewalk designed for aesthetics but then pedestrians cut through the grass and create their own path?  Yeah, that is this.  You will never stop pedestrians crossing here, so make it safer for them to do so.
Speed is a problem on 43rd Ave.  Cars blast through all the time.  It would be nice to see the addition of something to help slow them down.

Can you please update your development page with an update on WHERE this lot stands for redevelopment?  When will community engagement happen?  When will atlatus actualy do something with the tax break given to them to purchase and develop the land?

This is a dangerous place for all.  The width of the road affects pedestrians, the placement of transit stops makes this a defacto unmarked pedestrian crossing.  I would like to see pedestrian improvements here, like the addition of a pedestrian initiated traffic signal and marked crossing with island barriers for safety.  Additionally, this stretch of Central has a lot of jaywalking,  Couldn't we make use of a center island barrier (think of County road C in roseville near the Oval/City hall where the city has beautiful plants, trees, and bushes that both make the corridor look nice but also persuade pedestrians to walk to the nearest marked crossing.

As others have said, add marked crosswalks back in.  The bridge should be signed for students to use and encourage students to cross via the bridge for enhanced safety during the higher pedestrian traffic times.  This is an instance of going against the flow of pedestrians who are telling you how they will cross.  You should make efforts to make the way they will cross safer.   Again, you will NEVER get people to use the bridge as long as the intersection exisits as is.  It is a far cheaper solution to paint crosswalks, add pedestrian signals, and leverage your center islands as pedestrian safe havens.  In many other cities, they have a fenced area on the island so that if the signal expires midway, they can safely wait for the next signal opportunity.  Far more effective than the bridge no one uses.
49th, given it's width and schools, is another excellent candidate for makred bike lanes.   Connect the Mathaire Park trails to the main street pedestrian and bike path.
Cars speed down this street, there is a dip on 46th and 5th st and we always here a loud bang from the car ricocheting from the pavement, from how fast they were going.
properties.Name: Maribel Silva

properties.Comment: It would be nice to add side walks to 45th street. Ever since I moved here, I always want to walk to the plaza on Central Ave. but it’s so scary walking on the bare street with cars flying down.  When I go for walks with my kids I try to avoid walking there because of how many crashes there have been on the corner of 45th and 5th.
properties.Name: Maribel Silva

properties.Comment: Cars speed through here we need speed bumps!!

The constant speeding from Central to Reservoir Blvd. on 44th Ave is ridiculous. They put a speed monitor there last year and it helped for that time period but it went back to speeding when it was removed. It's dangerous trying to get out of your driveway and worse, little kids live on 44th. I'm afraid one of them will be hit. What's wrong with people? The past few years have been horrible.
properties.Name: Julie Blanch

properties.Comment:
People blow through stop signs and speed through the intersection at Arthur and 41st all the time. Pretty frequent accident occur at the intersection. There is currently a 2 way stop sign here with flashing lights on them, but that isn’t enough.

This should be a 4 way stop sign at minimum.
properties.Name: Christopher Bohne

properties.Comment: There are no sidewalks in this area.  When walking my kids to school it always feels dangerous, especially with all the people speeding down the curved streets.
properties.Name: Shannon

properties.Comment: People are constantly zooming up the hill on 45th. We have a lot of kids riding bikes around this intersection and I live in fear of one getting hit.
Very scary to cross whole walking
properties.Name: Jada Fehn

properties.Comment: very unsafe, even with the addition of the 'crosswalk' sign. cars consistently speed through here. i've had vulgar comments yelled out windows at me on several occasions.

Crosswalk signal across Reservoir is on walk when Central ave lights are green going North.  Way too many people take that turn onto Reservoir too quickly and do not realize the walk signal is on.  It's not a safe road crossing.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: People fly down 5th between 37th and 44th because there aren’t stop signs. It’s super scary! I wish we had a little boulevard strip or roundabout or stop sign to slow people down.
properties.Name: Sarah

properties.Comment: Flashing speed sign has not been effective.  Most are still exceeding the speed limit.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: There needs to be a right turn lane here. This gets really backed up due to left turn issues on both sides. Very busy intersection in the morning due to the charter school traffic and busses.
properties.Name: Sarah

properties.Comment: We need left arrows at this intersection to go from 53rd onto university. It’s a very scary intersection to turn left and it’s a short light.
properties.Name: Sarah

properties.Comment: We'd love a speed hump or two on 7th st by McKenna park. Drivers fly by the park at high speeds.
properties.Name: Amanda surko

properties.Comment: Traffic flies around this corner and cuts the corner tight.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: Central is a nightmare to bike.  Make a bike lane on one side of the road or both instead of making bikers go back and forth across the road.
properties.Name: Andrea Meisner

properties.Comment: Sidewalk stops mid-block, forced into street.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: NE side of intersection is poorly lit.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: Install tiny peanut roundabout to accommodate angled intersection and to slow traffic speeds.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: Install tiny peanut roundabout to accommodate angled intersection and to slow traffic speeds.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: Street is awkardly sized for 2 travel lanes in each direction and a parking lane, especially in winter.  Reduce effective width of street to make more friendly to pedestrians.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: Eastbound, unclear which lane corresponds to which lane at 40th and Central.
properties.Name: John Farmer

properties.Comment: It'd be great to re-paint this crosswalk at a minimum. But it'd be even better to add sidewalks on both sides of 44th from the bridge to university.
properties.Name: Annie

properties.Comment: This trail should be extended to connect to 40th.
Arthur Street is in desperate need of repavement. Add some sidewalks and protected bike lanes too.
This bridge is not accessible by bike due to stairs.
This is one of the most dangerous intersections I cross. People always creep up to the crosswalk when it's my turn to cross. Plus 6 lanes of traffic!
Please add an eastbound stop sign at this intersection
properties.Name: Mike Giralico

properties.Comment: Would love to see traffic calling measures taken on our street. This street is often used as a bypass to get to the high school in the mornings and it can become quite crazy before and after school.
properties.Name: Dana Borris

properties.Comment: Any allowance for pedestrians in this area would be appreciated. Whether that be a dedicated sidewalk or a protected Lane of some sort.
properties.Name: Dana Borris

properties.Comment: Add bike lane or path along 44th to connect to the Mississippi river trail in Fridley
properties.Name: Jason Kelley

properties.Comment: The constant speeding from Central to Reservoir Blvd. on 44th Ave is ridiculous. They put a speed monitor there last year and it helped for that time period but it went back to speeding when it was removed. It's dangerous trying to get out of your driveway and worse, little kids live on 44th. I'm afraid one of them will be hit. What's wrong with people? The past few years have been horrible.
properties.Name: Julie Blanch

properties.Comment: Lots of folks speed on this particular stretch of jefferson. I would like to see speed bumps or curb outs. Anything to reduce the speed. You cannot see over the crest of the hill from the bottom
properties.Name: Matt S

properties.Comment: Cars are driving through stop signs, sometimes drag racing, too.
There is no safe way to walk from nearby residences to the shops of Hilltop. People have to walk or bike on the street. There are not bike lanes or sidewalks.
A right turn lane for going to Aldi's would relieve congestion.
Walking along 44th is dangerous. There is nothing to stop cars from hitting pedestrians or bikers
Add soccer fields! Community members love to get outside and play sports, including soccer.

Walking along central with my young child is, quite frankly, terrifying. Despite living only a few blocks away, we often drive to Dairy Queen or the Library because otherwise it's like walking along a highway. The traffic is way too fast and not aware of pedestrians. We should have a calm, walkable "main street" especially if we want to encourage more businesses. We are primed for more foot traffic with the new apartment building, and with DQ, the Library, City Hall, Heights Theater and several restaurants all in this area, it should be comfortable for residents to walk amongst these businesses. Other towns have successfully slowed down and improved the presence of their main street, so we should take cues from what others have done -- lower speed limit, speed bumps, etc.
properties.Name: Lindsay

properties.Comment: We need sidewalks in this neighborhood to improve walkability and keep everyone safe.
There's no stop or yield signage at this three-way intersection. Cars just have to assume that Buchanan St traffic should stop.
properties.Name: Drew

properties.Comment: 39th is an important access road for many pedestrians, but traffic goes much too fast due to wide road and no stops between Reservoir and Johnson St.
properties.Name: Drew

properties.Comment: There are two intersections on 40th that feel dangerous as a pedestrian, with cars speeding down the hill from Resevoir and rolling through (or completely ignoring) the stop signs at Tyler and Polk Sts.
properties.Name: Drew

properties.Comment: Sightlines for turning from 39th onto Resevoir are dangerous. Angle of intersection is too severe.
properties.Name: Drew

properties.Comment: Sidewalk on north side of 40th between Polk and Tyler is in need of repair.
properties.Name: Drew

properties.Comment: sidewalk curbs have large bumps and are not friendly to anyone on wheels or with a stroller.
properties.Name: Drew

properties.Comment: Folks are speeding down this street.
It would be very helpful to add a stop sign here. It feels unsafe to cross the street and many cars assume it is a 4 way stop which has led to many accidents.

All of 45th Ave from Main to Stinson should be narrowed by using sidewalk, protected/raised bike lanes, landscapng, and corner bump outs.  This street could be beautiful  and used for bike/predestrians a lot more, but instead we have unmaintatined asphalt shoulders that are left unused.  Prioritize people over cars.
properties.Name: Jose

properties.Comment: Reservoir to 44th ave to stinson should be a beautiful bike and pedestrian cooridor.  The street for reservoir has no perceivable need to be as wide as it is for cars alone.  Narrow the road, bring out the curbs and add sidewalks and raised bike lanes to both sides.  Bump out all the corners and mark all intersections with crosswalks.  Add a stop light to the 4oth ave intersection.  Take these wider streets that clearly have no need to support traffic and make it easier for your residents to bike/walk to transit, parks, and other trails.
properties.Name: Jose

properties.Comment: Supplement the crosswalk with a pedestrian activated crossing signal (similar to what MPLS did on Johnson at 22nd ave).  I don't know why Cities don'e use pedestrian crossing signals more.  They can be powered by solar and batteries, from a technology standpoint that can't be too hard to implement, and they can really help any crosswalk be safer by alerting drivers to pedestrians being present.
properties.Name: Jose

properties.Comment: This intersection is very intimidating for pedestrians and bikers.  I would like to see the center medians used as pedestrian islands.  Install some nice retaining walls, add signal buttons for pedestrians, and make it so the intersection could be crossed in 2 stages.  Bump out the curbs a bit more and use better quality reflective markings for the crosswalks.
properties.Name: Jose

properties.Comment: Stop sign makes no sense.  The stop sign should be removed from Stinson both directions as stopping on the slope when roads are icy is not safe.  If speed is a concern, then other traffic calming measures should be considered (bump out the corners, narrow the road and add sidewalks instead of making pedestrians walk on the asphalt).
properties.Name: Jose

properties.Comment: People run the stop sign going east and west on 37th constantly.
properties.Name: Amy

properties.Comment: This street is not safe for the residents that live on it. We need a sidewalk and bike lane.
Library is located on this corner, it would be great to have a crosswalk here so people can get there safely, and not have to walk down to a traffic light.
properties.Name: Brent B

properties.Comment: Challenging as no sidewalk exists and this is a busy road that folks drive too fast on.
properties.Name: Genna Anderson

properties.Comment: Sidewalk for safety is needed.  Not safe as cars zip past very fast and close to shoulder and when cars are parked on shoulder of 45th it is even more dangerous to walk. Suggest connect sidewalk to where new brighton’s ends and continue sidewalk on to Reservoir (preferred) or at least to where 45th “bends” into Arthur.
properties.Name: Genna Anderson

properties.Comment: Jefferson has a serious speeding issue. This is a residential road and I've seen people doing 35+ up and down the length of it.
bike lane on central down to NE min would be nice
Sidewalks along Tyler Street would be pretty great. Cars seem to treat Tyler ST as a thoroughfare and walking the dogs or kids is getting pretty sketchy. Sidewalks would help.

If you're trying to get to Jefferson from Target, you need to turn left here, because there's no left turn at the stop light a block down, due to a single block of one way traffic. This is a very awkward place to turn left and can cause traffic backups.
A DOG PARK WOULD BE AMAZING

There are currently signs that say "No turn on red." No one obeys these. Almost every time I use the intersection from Reservoir Boulevard trying to get onto central, I almost get hit by someone on 37th trying to turn right on a red. Move the signs closer to the offending traffic, or make more signs, or make them more visible.

95% of the traffic here turns onto University. Which actually makes it super difficult to go straight, because you find someone making a turn in front of you. We need light controlled turns here similar to other Central intersections.
Cars coming down the hill from Resevoir, or coming from the Johnson ST turn sometimes blow right through the stop signs on 40th. I'm not sure what the solution is but it is a safety hazard.

love the new median to prevent the back ups by Starbucks and Discount tire. However, many folks are now making u-turns eastbound to westbound 53rd endangering pedistrians trying to cross 53rd on the west side of central and cars going southbound turning westbound. Needs a no u turn sign and enforcement.
4-way stop would make this intersection safer for pedestrians, bikers and motorists. The kids leaving school are at risk here as well.
properties.Name: MW

properties.Comment: 4-way stop would make this intersection safer for pedestrians, bikers and motorists. The kids leaving school are at risk here as well.
4-way stop would make this intersection safer for pedestrians, bikers and motorists. The kids leaving school are at risk here as well.
4-way stop would make this intersection safer for pedestrians, bikers and motorists. The kids leaving school are at risk here as well.

The new left turn and thru/right turn lanes are helpful, but many people ignore the signage or are not seeing it. When the light turns green, people in the left turn lane consistently speed up and pull in front of cars in the thru lane when they realize they are not in the thru lane. How can we improve this?

I appreciate this trail as a pedestrian  walking path, but it is very beat up asphalt. Walking downhill (southbound)  can be dangerous. It is also full of graffiti, litter, and overgrown weeds. A little maintenance could really clean this up.
I am regularly confused by the one stop sign at this intersection. As a pedestrian out for a morning constitutional, I am not sure why it is not an "all-way" stop instead of only northbound.
Fix this horrible intersection. Since the stop sign install at 42 and Madison it’s a drag strip from Jefferson to Quincy.
properties.Name: David Payne

properties.Comment: The parking for Łomianki Park is rough. The street parking is okay, but not great for turning around to face the right direction.
Light at 41st and Central rarely changes going east/west. This leads to cars running yellows/racing for the light due to the wait for the change.
Pedestrian crossings along 40th are ignored more often than followed. As a pedestrian I often need to wait until 4-5 cars go through my crossing before safely crossing the street.
People ignore the one-ways on Quincy, Jefferson, etc.
Sidewalk expansion similar to 37th would be fantastic. Sidewalks are small compared to traffic lanes all along 40th

I have used the intersection at 44th and University for the past 33 years. A left turn light needs to be added for traffic on 44th Avenue. In lieu of a light, the signage needs to reflect that the traffic lane is for both left turns and straight-ahead traffic. The parking lane is only for right hand turns. Because the volume of traffic has increased over the years, there has been increased use of the parking lane by traffic wanting to go straight through the intersection. This creates a situation where people are afraid to turn left because they believe cars will hit them.
properties.Name: Mark Emme

properties.Comment: Uncontrolled intersection - this should have stop signs at it.
properties.Name: Nikki Noteboom

properties.Comment: Get rid of those bollards blocking a proper right turn from westbound 44th onto northbound Central.
At minimum add cross walk marks on the street. Would be great to add a pedestrian activated flashing lights.
properties.Name: Andrea

properties.Comment: Need a stop sign on 50th at Washington. Drivers and pedestrians crossing 51st southbound can't see up over the hill for speeding cars.
The traffic on 43rd Ave going East from Central is dangerous as the cars travel about 50 to 60 mph by the time they get to the stop sign on Pierce and they very seldom stop for it.
properties.Name: Lynda and Art Wedlund

properties.Comment: Add speed bump or other safety measures related to crosswalk into McKenna Park. Repaint crosswalk/add additional signage.
30 mph is too fast down this hill
White crosswalk paint would be nice here for joggers and bikers coming from Silver Lake. Cars go fast down this hill
More signage on this stretch to watch for bikers
Traffic Speed on Stinson Blvd. Many Family walk down Stinson. There is also a school, and bus stops on Stinson. Speed bums would be a great help in slowing traffic.
properties.Name: Renee Sawyer

properties.Comment: Street Parking on Gould is out of hand. The City added offices and apartments without adequate parking for the apartment. It is difficult to drive down Gould and home owners are inconvenienced because of a poor planning by the city. The City needs to fix the problem.
properties.Name: Renee Sawyer

properties.Comment:
I bike thousands of miles a year within a 30 mile radius. I live on this street and have to cross here often. It is one I consider dangerous and requires extreme caution for right-turning cars, left-turning cars and cars running red lights.
On either side of the intersection are driveways with frequent traffic that adds extra danger for bikes.
Turning cars often try to squeeze by ahead of bikes and peds in the crosswalks.
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment:
Only at the very end of 50th can walkers get out of the street. Crossing Central is very dangerous even with a clear walk sign. Right-turning cars on both sides try to squeeze past. My wife and I have both had close encounters.
Put a camera here and see the chaos!
PS Drivers son't like the white posts but they make pedestrians more visible in my opinion.
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment: Pedestrians crossing from the bus stop often find left-turning cars cutting through the cross walk ahead of (or nearly into) them.
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment: For bikes, some intersections are important because they connect longer routes. IMO, crossing Central at 49/50th or 37th is key to riding to Main Street, or Columbia Parkway to get to East and West River routes using the viaduct. Main St and the path along the River thru the park are two safe ways to get north of 694 on a bike. They are also key to getting to the 7th St underpass (now excellent for biking.) Conversely, from west of Central, 49th/50th crossings are key to getting to the Matterhorn bridge. These important connecting crossings should be made safe.
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment: When pedestrians get a walk light to cross 50th, cars from Central do not have a green light to turn across them. But when pedestrians get a walk light to cross Central, cars from 50th get a "left turn allowed" light. Why not separate the two? Let pedestrians go first. Also add a bright flashing light when a pedestrian is in the crosswalk (i.e. he had pushed the button for the walk signal)?
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment: Intersection of Central, Reservoir, and 37th needs better signage or enforcement. Many drivers turn right onto Central in violation of signs. I've witnessed a number of close calls when Reservoir has green and 37th drivers turn right on red into them.

Yesterday, 9/13/2024, my wife and I were first in line at a red light at this corner. There was also a young man who had pushed the button to cross Central. Steady traffic on Central kept us waiting our turn. Then the light turned green for east-bound traffic on 50th, across from us. The signal was first a green arrow for left turners. The pedestrian waited for his light; then he started walking when the walk light came on. When he was near the middle of the northbound side of Central, another car made a left turn. I honked to alert both the car and the walker. The car thankfully passed just ahead of the walker.
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment: Continuation of the 9/13/2024 pedestrian nearly struck. IMO the lights should be adjusted so that the pedestrian gets a walk signal BEFORE left-turners get their signal. Just 20-30 seconds would let them get at least to the median.
properties.Name: Tom Kehrwald

properties.Comment: Too many red-light runners.  Could there be cameras?
Cars do not slow down to 30 mph as indicated by speed sign.
Accidents and near misses happen at this intersection frequently
properties.Name: Jessica

properties.Comment: Cars dive fast down Arthur. It has few stop signs. The markings on the street make it look like a highway. The "parking lanes" that are marked help give walkers or bikers a space, but the pavement is in bad condition in the parting lane. It is difficult to feel safe walking or biking on this street.
properties.Name: jessica

properties.Comment: Accessing these businesses on foot or bike is not easy.
properties.Name: jessica

properties.Comment: This street needs sidewalks that span the entire length. People drive too fast down this street and walking in the "parking lanes" does not feel safe.
properties.Name: jessica

properties.Comment: Turning onto Central south from Reservoir takes a long time and the light is very short.
properties.Name: jessica

properties.Comment: This is a 4-way stop that people often do not stop at. There is a lot of horn honking.  I think this, or other intersections on Arthur could benefit from ways to slow cars down and stop at stop signs. Maybe a roundabout or something?
properties.Name: jessica

properties.Comment: This intersection (coming from Johnson to 40th) is difficult to navigate and see oncoming traffic.
properties.Name: Jessica

properties.Comment: Need a sidewalk on 39th from Reservoir going east.
Need a sidewalk on the northern portion of Reservoir.
Very dangerous crosswalk.  Cars fly through it many times when people are trying to cross the road.
properties.Name: Connie

properties.Comment: No sidewalk.  People walk along the north side of this road between Tyler and Central.
I see people walk along this road and others in this area.  No sidewalks.
I see many people walking along this road too and from Central Avenue. No sidewalks.
properties.Name: Connie

properties.Comment: Cars drive too fast on this road.

PLEASE do something about the speeders from Central to Reservoir Blvd on 44th Ave NE. Speeding cars/motorcycles are ridiculous 24 hrs a day. I have had cars jump onto the hill in front of my house and left a license plate!  Speed signs don't help because there's no one to stop/tag them. There are little kids on this long block. School bus'  stop to pickup/drop off kids.  Winter time they slide sideways down the hill. DO SOMETHING!!!
properties.Name: Julie Blanch

properties.Comment:
This is the ONLY intersection, close to a city park playground, that does not have a crosswalk.  

I have photos to show this, I went to every single CH park with a playground. 

I am a resident of 3960 Cleveland, and see lots of children, strollers, bikes, attempt to cross 40th. 

I requested this years ago, the city did a "speed study" on 40th ???? That was useless, naturally the request was denied. 

I then called last year and was told my request would be forwarded to a new commission being formed? 

Even in the Winter, children are crossing to go sledding on the small hill. 

Why do all other parks get a crosswalk, but not Prestemon Park? 

I recall that Lomianki (west) may not have had one, but the streets there are not travelled much. 

Please, a stop sign, a crosswalk, something.  20+ years I have seen little ones bolt across the street, so sad.
properties.Name: Monica Duffy

properties.Comment: People speed up & down this road all hours of the day/night.
properties.Name: Mary Granlund

properties.Comment: Sidewalk literally ends at the house before 44th & Tyler. It’s not safe for anyone but especially not safe for students walking to school.
properties.Name: Mary Granlund

properties.Comment: Would love to see bike lanes that extend Jefferson for the kids biking to school. No safe path for them.
Biking for kids heading to school is not safe here. They need a straight shot with room for bikes.
Unsafe storm sewer grates in this location. Bike tires can call through grates that run parallel to the street.
properties.Name: Aaron Chirpich

properties.Comment: Unsafe storm sewer grates in the vicinity of this intersection. Grates run parallel to the street and bike tires can fall through.
Fix or make school change traffic pattern around prodeo Academy. On university frontage, 4th Street from 40th to 44th.
properties.Name: Matthew Reynolds

properties.Comment: must make intersection right turn only coming off Gould. Traffic is horrible due to excessive cars from residents not parking under building
ratio residents block access to theatre, DQ, church. parking on gould  from Ratio entrance and parking lot entrance to Central should be posted as 15 MIN max for the DQ and the Bank.

There is a lot of foot and bike traffic (a lot of kids) on 44th and no sidewalk. I have witnessed at least one accident with a pedestrian at the corner of 44th and 7th. Cars fly down this road. We need a sidewalk.
properties.Name: Crystal Hambley

properties.Comment: This block on 7th (from 44th to 43rd) doesn’t haven any sidewalks. There is a lot of foot traffic (my family of 6 walks this road daily and we are constantly dodging cars who are speeding around the corner onto 7th from 44th or coming down the hill on 7th from 43rd). This is especially scary in the winter with no sidewalk. There also is no light in this corner of the road on 7th for half the block. It is very dangerous for pedestrians. I have witnessed a bike/MVA accident at this corner. I don’t think people coming down the hill at night always see the stop sign. We could use another light in this area.
properties.Name: Crystal Hambley

properties.Comment: This is an uncontrolled intersection. I think there should be a 2way stop or at least a yield here for Cleveland.
A lot of people walk to the convenience store and bus stop, but there's no sidewalk. It's especially dangerous right next to the gas station.
There are no sidewalks on any of these frontage roads next to hwy 47. There are lots of businesses here that are only accessible by car, even though they're right next to the neighborhood.
There is no curb cut to get onto the bike trail here.

During rush hour it is next to impossible to to get across the north bound traffic on Central Ave in order to take a left onto south bound traffic.     And,  without a crosswalk for decades it’s a dangerous intersection for pedestrians.  They will cross with or without a crosswalk.
properties.Name: Laura Barton

properties.Comment: Cars speeding on 44th Ave NE/ Central to Res. Bl. is out of control.  We need speed bumps or something to slow them down. MC's and cars show no regard for anyone. Something needs to be done ASAP
properties.Name: Julie Blanch

properties.Comment: Very dangerous to cross. Cars speed both directions. There are no pedestrian aids-stop signs, crosswalks., speed bumps. We need sidewalks on both sides of 44th.
properties.Name: Emi

properties.Comment:
Due to the amount of cars bottoming-out as they speed through this intersection it may be a wise idea to introduce a 4-way stop or some other traffic control measures.

With a Mosque, a Church, a daycare, and many other pedestrians, this is a high foot traffic area, too.
Even with North/South yield signs, people are not slowing. There is a daycare, church, and mosque, all nearby.
Kids are crossing to get to their school bus stop and cars fly by.

There have been multiple accidents at this intersection. The latest, the traffic did yield but didn’t realize how fast the cross traffic was going, as many going way too fast in this area. We need a four way stop
properties.Name: Katie Glenn

properties.Comment: There's this super odd T intersection on 50th and Tyler near the Jimmy John's here in Columbia Heights. There's no signage to slow the flow of traffic that spills from Tyler to 50th, and in my estimation and observation, it's an unwise to keep this spot unregulated. This area is already bustling enough as there are multiple commercial spaces nearby.
properties.Name: Aaron Chirpich

properties.Comment: 49th between Jefferson and Central. So much speeding on the road outside of school hours. Consider speed bumps in front of school entrance or at Madison.
This stretch of 49th would be a good location for a MUP or separated bike lane to allow kids to safely bike to school from the surrounding neighborhoods.
properties.Name: Matt Laue

properties.Comment: Lots of pedestrian traffic on this road, but no sidewalks.

Cars drive way too fast down this road.  And no one seems to care.  We have asked multiple times for a speed hump or 2 and the city keeps saying it's too hard for the snow plows to navigate.  I've talked to plenty of plow drivers who say it's easily handled.  Something needs to be done.  I would love to see the city trying to prevent the death of a child, rather than respond to one.
properties.Name: Anonymous
